text: Pag-asa is a Tagalog language word meaning "hope". It may refer to: * PAGASA - Philippine Atmospheric, Geophysical and Astronomical Services Administration * Pag-asa, Bohol - one of the 44 barangays of the municipality of Ubay, in the Philippines province of Bohol * Pag-asa (eagle) - the name given to the first of the breed "Philippine eagle" to be bred and hatched in captivity * Pag-asa - the Philippine name of Thitu Island, one of the Spratly Islands in the South China Sea / West Philippine Sea ==See also== *Pagasa (disambiguation)
title: Pag-asa
